# User-Facing Terminology

Use this terminology dictionary whenever writing or reviewing text that can be
seen by app users: Flutter widgets, localization ARB files, HTML mocks, help
text, settings labels, dialogs, snackbars, notifications, and documentation-like
UI copy.

Technical terms are allowed in developer-facing surfaces: function names,
methods, classes, modules, internal comments when useful, tests, debug logs,
developer tools, console output, OpenSpec implementation notes, and chat with
the developer.

## Dictionary

| Technical term | Do not show to users | User-facing wording |
| --- | --- | --- |
| fork / forker / forkable | Do not use “fork” or “forker” in app UI copy. | Use “create a derived version”, “derived version”, “version dérivée”, or the locale-appropriate equivalent. |
| owner (sharing) | Prefer product role name in UI. | **FR:** Propriétaire; use locale-appropriate equivalent elsewhere. |
| borrower (sharing) | Prefer product role name in UI. | **FR:** Emprunteur; use locale-appropriate equivalent elsewhere. |
| engine hour meter (boat) | Do not treat **horomètre** as jargon or invent alternate FR labels. Use the official user-facing term per locale. | **FR:** Horomètre (official term, [OQLF GDT](https://vitrinelinguistique.oqlf.gouv.qc.ca/fiche-gdt/fiche/2076698/horometre)); **FR (France, if regional copy is offered):** Horamètre; **EN:** Engine hour meter; **ES:** Cronómetro del motor |
| odometer gap / differential | Do not use developer jargon in the prompt; no in-app dispute workflow. | **FR:** « À qui le différentiel de {amount} est-il attribuable ? »; **Unknown:** **Inconnu** / **Je ne sais pas**; **EN/ES:** locale-appropriate equivalent |
| meter reading photo | Required for every reading; supports negative-gap verification. | **FR:** Photo de l'odomètre (or **Horomètre** for boats) — required, not optional |

## Rule Of Thumb

If the text is for a real-world user, prefer product language over developer
language. If the text is for developers or the AI, the technical term may remain.
